<chapter id="chap-Best_Practices_Guide-OVM" lang="en-US">
	<title>Oracle VM (OVM)</title>
	 <para>
		<indexterm>
			<primary>hypervisors</primary>
			<secondary>Oracle VM (OVM)</secondary>
		</indexterm>

	</para>
	 <section id="sect-Best_Practices_Guide-OVM-Installation">
		<title>Installation</title>
		 <para>

		</para>
		 <section id="sect-Best_Practices_Guide-OVM-Installation-Prerequisites">
			<title>Prerequisites and Constraints</title>
			 <para>
				All OVM Hosts must follow these guidelines:
			</para>
			 <itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Must be 64-bit.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				 <listitem>
					<para>
						Must support HVM (Intel-VT or AMD-V enabled).
					</para>
				</listitem>
				 <listitem>
					<para>
						Within a single cluster, the hosts must be homogenous. The CPUs must be of the same type, count, and feature flags.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				 <listitem>
					<para>
						<indexterm>
							<primary>hypervisors</primary>
							<secondary>Oracle VM (OVM)</secondary>
							<tertiary>kernel versions</tertiary>
						</indexterm>
						Within a single cluster, the hosts must be of the same kernel version.
					</para>
				</listitem>

			</itemizedlist>

		</section>
		

	</section>
	

